text.0: Viral posts on Facebook falsely claim there were more votes cast in the 2020 election in Wisconsin than there were registered voters. The number of registered voters exceeded the votes cast by nearly 388,000, as of Nov. 1. https://t.co/H8UpJKjEYn #FactCHAT
text.1: A data input error that briefly showed an unusually large uptick in votes for Joe Biden in Michigan prompted suspicions online and an unfounded claim of voter fraud. Turned out to be a typo by a county official that was quickly corrected. https://t.co/8sXhE1X0vv #FactCHAT
text.2: In Wisconsin, Trump falsely claimed the state’s dairy farms were “decimated” under the Obama/Biden administration but “now … are doing very well,” and he greatly overstated the potential impact of the USMCA trade pact. https://t.co/D8wXGUTu22 #FactCHAT
